              <option name="originalContent" value="# Any Video Downloader (Flask + yt-dlp)&#10;&#10;A personal-use web app to fetch and download media from many public platforms supported by `yt-dlp` (including YouTube, Instagram, LinkedIn, Snapchat, Twitter/X where publicly accessible).&#10;&#10;## Features&#10;&#10;- Category modes: **Video** and **MP3**&#10;- Default high quality for both modes&#10;- Selectable quality options for video and MP3 bitrate&#10;- **English subtitles only** (auto when available)&#10;- Live progress details:&#10;  - percent&#10;  - elapsed time&#10;  - ETA&#10;  - download speed&#10;  - downloaded size / total size&#10;- Automatic file download trigger after completion&#10;- Optional cookies input prompt for private/age-restricted content&#10;- Responsive UI for mobile and desktop&#10;- Health endpoint: `/health`&#10;&#10;## Important limitations&#10;&#10;- Private, members-only, age-restricted, or login-required content can fail without valid cookies.&#10;- This app does **not** bypass platform restrictions.&#10;- Render instances use ephemeral disk. Downloaded files are temporary.&#10;- FFmpeg is required for merged video and MP3 conversion.&#10;&#10;## Local run&#10;&#10;```bash&#10;python -m venv .venv&#10;.venv\Scripts\activate&#10;pip install -r requirements.txt&#10;python app.py&#10;```&#10;&#10;Open:&#10;&#10;- `http://127.0.0.1:5000`&#10;- `http://127.0.0.1:5000/health`&#10;&#10;## Render deployment&#10;&#10;This repo now includes:&#10;&#10;- `Procfile`&#10;- `runtime.txt`&#10;- `render.yaml`&#10;&#10;If you configure manually in Render Web Service:&#10;&#10;- Build Command: `pip install -r requirements.txt`&#10;- Start Command: `gunicorn -b 0.0.0.0:$PORT main:app`&#10;&#10;Also ensure FFmpeg is available in your runtime.&#10;&#10;## Vercel deployment&#10;&#10;This repo includes:&#10;&#10;- `vercel.json`&#10;- `.vercelignore`&#10;&#10;Quick deploy with Vercel CLI:&#10;&#10;```bash&#10;npm i -g vercel&#10;vercel login&#10;vercel&#10;vercel --prod&#10;```&#10;&#10;Notes for Vercel:&#10;&#10;- This app runs as a Python serverless function from `main.py`.&#10;- Function timeout is configured in `vercel.json` (`maxDuration`).&#10;- Long downloads can hit serverless execution/time limits.&#10;- Temp files are ephemeral in serverless environments.&#10;&#10;## Quick verification&#10;&#10;1. Open `/` and confirm UI loads.&#10;2. Open `/health` and confirm `{&quot;ok&quot;: true, ...}`.&#10;3. Use `Fetch Info` with a public URL.&#10;4. Start a download and confirm progress updates and auto-download trigger.&#10;&#10;## Policy &amp; legal&#10;&#10;Use only for content you own or have rights/permission to download.&#10;# Media-Downloader&#10;&#10;" />
              <option name="updatedContent" value="# Any Video Downloader (Flask + yt-dlp)&#10;&#10;A personal-use web app to fetch and download media from many public platforms supported by `yt-dlp` (including YouTube, Instagram, LinkedIn, Snapchat, Twitter/X where publicly accessible).&#10;&#10;## Features&#10;&#10;- Category modes: **Video** and **MP3**&#10;- Default high quality for both modes&#10;- Selectable quality options for video and MP3 bitrate&#10;- **English subtitles only** (auto when available)&#10;- Live progress details:&#10;  - percent&#10;  - elapsed time&#10;  - ETA&#10;  - download speed&#10;  - downloaded size / total size&#10;- Automatic file download trigger after completion&#10;- Optional cookies input prompt for private/age-restricted content&#10;- Responsive UI for mobile and desktop&#10;- Health endpoint: `/health`&#10;&#10;## Important limitations&#10;&#10;- Private, members-only, age-restricted, or login-required content can fail without valid cookies.&#10;- This app does **not** bypass platform restrictions.&#10;- Render instances use ephemeral disk. Downloaded files are temporary.&#10;- Vercel serverless has strict execution limits; long video jobs can timeout.&#10;- FFmpeg is required for merged video and MP3 conversion.&#10;&#10;## Cookies setup (recommended)&#10;&#10;For private/age-restricted videos, you can:&#10;&#10;1. Paste cookies in the UI (`cookies.txt` format), or&#10;2. Set environment variable `AVD_COOKIES_TEXT` in your hosting provider.&#10;&#10;If an auth error is detected, the UI prompts for cookies and retries automatically.&#10;&#10;## Local run&#10;&#10;```bash&#10;python -m venv .venv&#10;.venv\Scripts\activate&#10;pip install -r requirements.txt&#10;python app.py&#10;```&#10;&#10;Open:&#10;&#10;- `http://127.0.0.1:5000`&#10;- `http://127.0.0.1:5000/health`&#10;&#10;## Render deployment&#10;&#10;This repo now includes:&#10;&#10;- `Procfile`&#10;- `runtime.txt`&#10;- `render.yaml`&#10;&#10;If you configure manually in Render Web Service:&#10;&#10;- Build Command: `pip install -r requirements.txt`&#10;- Start Command: `gunicorn -b 0.0.0.0:$PORT main:app`&#10;&#10;Also ensure FFmpeg is available in your runtime.&#10;&#10;## Vercel deployment&#10;&#10;This repo includes:&#10;&#10;- `vercel.json`&#10;- `.vercelignore`&#10;&#10;Quick deploy with Vercel CLI:&#10;&#10;```bash&#10;npm i -g vercel&#10;vercel login&#10;vercel&#10;vercel --prod&#10;```&#10;&#10;Notes for Vercel:&#10;&#10;- This app runs as a Python serverless function from `main.py`.&#10;- Function timeout is configured in `vercel.json` (`maxDuration`).&#10;- Long downloads can hit serverless execution/time limits.&#10;- Temp files are ephemeral in serverless environments.&#10;&#10;## Quick verification&#10;&#10;1. Open `/` and confirm UI loads.&#10;2. Open `/health` and confirm `{&quot;ok&quot;: true, ...}`.&#10;3. Use `Fetch Info` with a public URL.&#10;4. Start a download and confirm progress updates and auto-download trigger.&#10;&#10;## Policy &amp; legal&#10;&#10;Use only for content you own or have rights/permission to download.&#10;# Media-Downloader&#10;&#10;" />
